<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1567.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 5th instant (No. 1063,) in relation to the course of the
                            Fenian movement, and to the denial by Mr. Gladstone and others of
                            complicity in the rebel loan.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary</hi>.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>